ore downloading the app onto their personal phones, there=E2=80=99s a palpa=
ble discomfort in rallying around the free speech
rights of a company under suspicion=E2=80=94especially one whose ownership =
is based in a country that bans <i>American</i> apps and movies without a s=
econd thought. Also: Just because we don=E2=80=99t know the precise basis f=
or the Biden administration=E2=80=99s national security concerns doesn=E2=
=80=99t mean they=E2=80=99re unfounded.<br/><br/>Based on my conversations,=
 however, Hollywood=E2=80=99s reluctance to speak up for TikTok may have as=
 much to do with old-fashioned rivalry. The app=E2=80=99s explosive growth =
